metadata.name: DOORS N KEYS FIRST COLLECTION: CONCEPTS - 016 - often -
metadata.description:
“The average person will have more than 6,000 thoughts in a single day”

It is shocking to discover how often our thoughts are in cycles of the same circumstances. 
The same fears… over and over again. Social anxiety, pressures and expectations, failure, disappointment…

We set ourselves up for success, just as we set ourselves up for failure.

Exposing all my flaws, accepting all my flaws, letting go of all my flaws.

Let go of all that weighs you down.

— rayseetoe -
